<!-- ============================================================
     FIVE FRUSTRATIONS, EXPANDED.
     The homepage names them. This page explains why each one happens
     and what OTP does about it. Each: quote -> why -> what changes.
     ============================================================ -->
<section class="bg-white py-20 sm:py-28 border-t border-gray-100">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
    <div class="text-[11px] text-gray-500 tracking-[0.18em] uppercase mb-4 font-medium">
      What you are saying about your AI team
    </div>
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 leading-[1.08] tracking-tight max-w-3xl mb-4">
      Five frustrations. Same root cause.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-600 leading-[1.6] max-w-2xl mb-14">
      These are not five separate problems. They are five symptoms of the same thing &mdash; your AI is doing real work without a seat on your chart.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-14 max-w-3xl">

      <!-- Frustration 1 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-5">
          <div class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-300 tracking-tight" style="font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;">1</div>
          <blockquote class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-gray-900 leading-[1.32] font-light italic" style="font-style: italic;">
            "My AI tools are scattered across 14 tabs."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-10 pl-0 sm:pl-12">
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gray-500 font-semibold mb-2">Why this happens</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">Each tool is a feature you bought, not a seat you placed. They have no relationship to each other and no relationship to the rest of your org. The chart in your head and the AI in your stack live in different files.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-otp-600 font-semibold mb-2">What OTP does</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">Every agent becomes a tile on the chart with an owner, a role, an authority level, and an accountability line. The same chart your humans live on.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Frustration 2 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-5">
          <div class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-300 tracking-tight" style="font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;">2</div>
          <blockquote class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-gray-900 leading-[1.32] font-light italic" style="font-style: italic;">
            "My senior people are drowning at hire seven."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-10 pl-0 sm:pl-12">
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gray-500 font-semibold mb-2">Why this happens</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">Coordination load scales linearly with each human you add. Senior people become full-time context-distribution machines. They are not exhausted from doing the work; they are exhausted from teaching it.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-otp-600 font-semibold mb-2">What OTP does</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">Agents read SOPs at every session. They do not need a Tuesday one-on-one. They do not interrupt at 6pm. The new headcount stops adding coordination overhead.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Frustration 3 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-5">
          <div class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-300 tracking-tight" style="font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;">3</div>
          <blockquote class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-gray-900 leading-[1.32] font-light italic" style="font-style: italic;">
            "The SOPs we wrote last quarter are already ignored."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-10 pl-0 sm:pl-12">
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gray-500 font-semibold mb-2">Why this happens</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">SOPs are documents. Documents are read by humans. Humans only read them when they remember to. The work happens in tools the document cannot reach. The decoupling between doc and runtime is the half-life of every BPM rollout.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-otp-600 font-semibold mb-2">What OTP does</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">SOPs become runtime context, read by the agent at every session. The human edits at noon, the agent that boots at 12:01 has the new version. The doc and the work converge.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Frustration 4 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-5">
          <div class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-300 tracking-tight" style="font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;">4</div>
          <blockquote class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-gray-900 leading-[1.32] font-light italic" style="font-style: italic;">
            "I genuinely don't know what each agent is actually doing."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-10 pl-0 sm:pl-12">
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gray-500 font-semibold mb-2">Why this happens</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">AI tools were bought feature-by-feature, not placed seat-by-seat. There is no chart, no scorecard, no audit trail. The thing running cold outreach has no name and no owner. That is the definition of shadow IT.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-otp-600 font-semibold mb-2">What OTP does</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">Each agent has a name, a role, a job description, a scorecard, and a human it reports to. You can answer "what is each agent doing" in one minute, by reading the chart.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Frustration 5 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-5">
          <div class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-300 tracking-tight" style="font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;">5</div>
          <blockquote class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-gray-900 leading-[1.32] font-light italic" style="font-style: italic;">
            "Every new agent gets re-explained from scratch."
          </blockquote>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-10 pl-0 sm:pl-12">
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gray-500 font-semibold mb-2">Why this happens</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">Agents start at zero each session unless given context. Manual context means a human typing the same paragraph into Claude every morning. The thing the human typed last week is gone.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-otp-600 font-semibold mb-2">What OTP does</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-[1.7]">Agents inherit SOPs from the human they report to at runtime. The next agent under your COO starts with everything the COO already authored. No re-explanation, no copy-paste, no day-one drift.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

